description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for an experienced communications professional to join a team that is passionate about improving early cancer diagnosis and cancer screening across the west Essex and Hertfordshire area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The project team will be implementing the national cancer screening programme, a piece of work to improve screening uptake rates across a range of cancers, raising awareness of symptoms and interventions that can prevent or avoid cancer occurring in the area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An integral part of the project team, the Cancer Campaign Manager will work closely with a wide range of stakeholders, both internally and externally, to develop, implement and evaluate a communications plan and activities based on the project team’s objectives. The successful candidate will be experienced in developing creative, proactive and targeted communications that encourage action.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the role the Cancer Campaign Manager will provide sound, professional advice and support on communications to senior officers and be able to work to tight deadlines, use their initiative, manage conflicting priorities and interpret complex data and information to inform their communications plan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;See the job description and person specification for full details.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Vanessa Moon&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Head of Communications and Engagement&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;vanessa.moon@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
